0matter.%3Cbr%3EAway%20to%20the%20bank%20I%20swam%20like%20a%20fish%2C%3Cbr%3EClimbed%20up%20on%20the%20shore%20then%20remembered%20my%20dive%20wish.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20moonbeams%20on%20the%20breast%20of%20the%20new-frozen%20ice%3Cbr%3EBetrayed%20the%20luster%20of%20nineteenth%20century%20objects%20below%20at%20least%20thrice%3Cbr%3EWhen%2C%20what%20did%20my%20wondering%20eyes%20see%2C%3Cbr%3EBut%20a%20miniature%20sleigh%2C%20filled%20with%20Blossom's%20for%20me!%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20little%20old%20driver%2C%20so%20lively%20even%20gonzo%2C%3Cbr%3EI%20knew%20in%20a%20moment%20it%20must%20be%20St.%20Alonzo.%3Cbr%3EMore%20rapid%20than%20eagles%20his%20draft%20horses%20they%20came%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20he%20whistled%2C%20and%20shouted%2C%20and%20called%20them%20by%20name%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%22Now%2C%20SEPHRENESS!%20now%2C%20VALENTINE!%20now%2C%20CHRISTOPHER%20and%20OTTO!%3Cbr%3EOn%2C%20CHARELES!%20on%20LOUIS!%20on%2C%20THEODOR%20and%20HIRAM!%3Cbr%3ETo%20the%20top%20of%20the%20bank!%20To%20the%20top%20of%20the%20sea%20wall!%3Cbr%3ENow%20dash%20away!%20dash%20away!%20dash%20away%20all!%22%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EAs%20dry%20leaves%20that%20before%20the%20wild%20hurricane%20fly%2C%3Cbr%3EWhen%20they%20meet%20with%20an%20obstacle%2C%20mount%20to%20the%20sky%2C%3Cbr%3ESo%20up%20to%20the%20house-tops%20the%20coursers%20they%20flew%2C%3Cbr%3EWith%20the%20sleigh%20full%20of%20Blossoms%2C%20and%20St.%20Alonzo%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20in%20a%20twinkling%2C%20I%20heard%20on%20the%20bank%3Cbr%3EThe%20prancing%20and%20pawing%20of%20each%20horse's%20flank.%3Cbr%3EAs%20I%20drew%20in%20my%20dive%20float%2C%20and%20was%20turning%20around%2C%3Cbr%3EDown%20the%20riverbank%20St.%20Alonzo%20came%20with%20a%20bound.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20dressed%20all%20in%20fur%2C%20from%20his%20head%20to%20his%20foot%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20his%20clothes%20were%20all%20tarnished%20with%20ashes%20and%20soot%3B%3Cbr%3EA%20six%20pack%20of%20bottles%20he%20had%20flung%20on%20his%20back%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20he%20looked%20like%20a%20peddler%20just%20opening%20his%20pack.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EHis%20bottles%20--%20how%20they%20twinkled!%20his%20pontils%20how%20merry!%3Cbr%3EHis%20blobs%20were%20like%20roses%2C%20his%20stoppers%20like%20a%20cherry!%3Cbr%3EHis%20droll%20little%20mouth%20was%20drawn%20up%20like%20a%20bow%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20the%20beard%20of%20his%20chin%20was%20as%20white%20as%20the%20snow%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EA%20crumpled%20up%20old%20Ale%20recipe%20he%20held%20tight%20in%20his%20teeth%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20the%20effervescence%20of%20its%20concoction%20encircled%20his%20head%20like%20a%20wreath%3B%3Cbr%3EHe%20had%20a%20broad%20face%20and%20a%20little%20beer%20belly%2C%3Cbr%3EThat%20shook%2C%20when%20he%20laughed%20like%20a%20bowlful%20of%20jelly.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20chubby%20and%20plump%2C%20a%20right%20jolly%20old%20elf%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20I%20laughed%20when%20I%20saw%20him%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20wanting%20to%20get%20one%20of%20his%20bottles%20for%20myself%3B%3Cbr%3EA%20wink%20of%20his%20eye%20and%20a%20twist%20of%20his%20head%2C%3Cbr%3ESoon%20gave%20me%20to%20know%20I%20had%20nothing%20to%20dread%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EHe%20spoke%20not%20a%20word%2C%20but%20went%20straight%20to%20his%20work%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20filled%20up%20my%20dive%20float%3B%20then%20turned%20with%20a%20jerk%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20laying%20his%20finger%20aside%20of%20his%20nose%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20giving%20a%20nod%2C%20up%20the%20riverbank%20he%20rose%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EHe%20sprang%20to%20his%20sleigh%2C%20to%20his%20team%20gave%20a%20whistle%2C%3Cbr%3EAnd%20away%20they%20all%20flew%20like%20the%20down%20of%20a%20thistle.%3Cbr%3EBut%20I%20heard%20him%20exclaim%2C%20ere%20he%20drove%20out%20of%20sight%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%22HAPPY%20CHRISTMAS%20TO%20ALL%2C%20AND%20TO%20ALL%20ENJOY%20A%20FRESH%20BLOSSOM'S%20BADGER%20ALE%20TONIGHT!%22%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22newsReadMore%22%20href%3D%22%2FWisconsinNews%22%3EReturn%20to%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A